  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0bca\u0bb4\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc6\u0ba3\u0bcd \u0bae\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc0\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b9c\u0bc2\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b89\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0baa\u0ba3\u0bb5\u0bc0\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Inflation rose in July, according to the Colombo Consumer Price Index",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "Inflation based on the Colombo Consumer Price Index rose significantly to 60.8 percent last July.",
        "While the inflation was recorded at 54.6 percent in June last year, it showed an increase of 6.2 percent in July.",
        "The Central Bank of Sri Lanka stated that the main reason for the rise in inflation is the increase in the prices of food items including palm, shellfish, rice and non-food items and services such as transport, water, electricity and gas charges in the last one month.",
        "As the country is facing a massive economic crisis, inflation is increasing rapidly due to the devaluation of the Sri Lankan rupee.",
        "In such a situation, according to the assessment carried out by the Colombo Consumer Price Index, inflation recorded a sharp increase in June compared to the previous month.",
        "In particular, the central bank pointed out that the monthly price increase of food and non-food items is the main reason for the increase in inflation. Food inflation, which was recorded at 80.1 percent in June last year, increased to 90.9 percent in July, and non-food inflation, which was 42.4 percent in June, increased to 46.5 percent in July.",
        "A report released by the Central Bank stated that a significant increase was observed in the prices of food items including palm, rice and shellfish last month, and in terms of non-food items, the prices and charges of transport, restaurants, hotels, housing, water, electricity, gas and other fuels increased.",
        "Meanwhile, the monthly change in the Colombo Consumer Price Index was recorded at 4.51 percent last July due to an increase in the prices of food and non-food items by 2.31 percent and 2.20 percent respectively.",
        "According to the survey, core inflation, which reflects the core inflation of the economy, rose to 44.3 percent in July from 39.9 percent last June.",
        "Meanwhile, annual average inflation rose to 16.7 percent in July from 13.3 percent in June.",
        "In such a background, it is noteworthy that while the inflation calculated according to the Colombo Consumer Price Index was recorded as 14.2, 15.1, 18.7, 29.8, 39.1 and 54.6 percent in the last six months of January, February, March, April, May and June, it has increased to 60.8 percent in the month of July."
      ],
